At p. 600, Peter Sans, not yet heretic, tells two heretics to tell some good words; this may well be Peter and Jacques but this is uncertain. Peter Sans admired Peter Autier before James was captured (p. 668, 774, 818). From the copious visiones of Peter Autier and Peter Sans, it seems that Peter Sans was the socius of Peter after James was captured. Also at p. 720, these are two groups and Jacques and Peter Sans are not in the same one. But we have this clear evidence at p. 880.
